<br>
Here is what I think is wrong, and what we as OOTW do not do anyhow. Lets say we need a shadowknight, and Pezgek from the Troll Patrol is a nice high lvl SK. Now We have interaction with Pezgek b/c of the alliance and through this interaction we court him to leave his guild and join ours. We give him items, we invite him on raids, we group with him constantly etc etc etc. In the end WE ASK him to leave the Troll Patrol and join us. That is Farming for members.<br>
<br>
What I think is valid, and what we as OOTW do do. We do NOT bribe, or actively presue, etc alliance Guilded members. However since these people have contact with us (like Bjarni) they get to know us and our playstyle and ethics. Now for whatever reason that person, I'll use Bjarni as an example. Has a falling out with his/her guild or is just dissatisfied with it in general. He then chooses to leave his guild in search of another. Now he knows various guilds and have friends in em, and his options are laid out before him. So HE APPROACHES guilds HE is intrested in. Because he approached us and yes we knew him from outside the guild, it just happened to be from the VA it is well within our right to invite him into the guild. We didn't steal anyone, they came to us of their own free will.<br>
<br>
I personally will not turn away good people from our guild regardless what their prior guild was. If the person expresses intrest in me and my guild, and requests to join I will take the offer seriously, based on that person's merits not their former ties. Grace periods my ass, I don't condone loosing perfectly good players like Bjarni, to another guild b/c we have to wait some 30 days to invite him, just b/c he was a former member of SOS. Now some officers may disagree with me on this matter as well as some VA reps. however I stand firm on this belief, and those people can take it up with me.<br>
<br>
Endnote: IF you are intrested in OOTW, thank you. Plz contact us in game and we will give you all the info you need about us. Rember you want to join us and that in itself is an honor for us, and we will respect your decision and treat it accordingly<br>
<br>
-Gersh</td></tr></table>
